Description:
Exceptional Quality, Versatility and Urban Convenience
Modern low-maintenance perfection, this surprisingly spacious 3BR home delivers an environment of absolute quality and floorplan flexibility along with close proximity to cosmopolitan Coburg's renowned lifestyle attractions. Designed to take full advantage of its northerly aspect, the home's light-filled interior showcases an extra-large upstairs master bedroom with private dressing room and stylish ensuite, two additional bedrooms (one on each level) and two additional bathrooms (one on each level). Add to this a central study area/retreat and expansive open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a beautifully-appointed kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances and walk-in pantry. Other features include a full-size laundry and under-stair storeroom, ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, alarm, double glazing, tinted windows, solid hardwood floors, square-set ceilings and stone benchtops throughout. Step outside to discover an undercover entertaining deck and private north-facing back garden, plus the added advantage of a remote-control double garage via rear ROW. Walking distance to all public transport options and the open spaces of Bush Reserve, it's also close to local schools, Coburg's renowned shopping precinct, as well as Sydney Road cafes and restaurants.
Parking Available in Cramer St or High St
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 276 Bell Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Spectacular opportunity
A spectacular opportunity to secure a single fronted period home that is set on an elevated corner allotment with presents. Whether you are looking for a residence to renovate and call home or an astute investor who understands value in superior location, this home will surely tempt all. Showcasing impressive high ceilings, two spacious bedrooms, tiled kitchen with meals area, functional appliances, dishwasher, formal lounge with fireplace, a large central bathroom, floorboards, front garden, undercover front porch, side driveway with plenty of off street parking and a secure lock up garage/workshop and an undercover entertaining area at the rear.
Brilliantly positioned in a family friendly neighbourhood of Coburg that is spoilt by Sydney Road shops/cafes/restaurants that offer a convenient lifestyle. Also situated close to multiple primary and secondary schools, Coburg Station, Sydney Road Tram, easy access to the CBD, Bell Street and so much more at your fingertips. Inspection a must.

Description:
Timeless Terrace in a Perfect Position
Tucked away in a secluded cul-de-sac yet moments from the buzz of Sydney Road, this single-front Victorian (c1890) provides a welcoming environment of immediate quality and comfort along with terrific scope to further enhance and expand in the future (STCA). One of four in a gorgeous row of attached terraces, the home's inviting interior comprises two generous bedrooms (both with full-height built-in robes), bathroom and separate laundry, spacious open lounge/dining area leading through to the timber-cabinet kitchen. Features include ducted heating, air conditioner (lounge area), high ceilings, plantation shutters and solid hardwood floors, plus a delightful back garden complete with undercover patio/entertaining area, extensive brick paving, handy storage shed and high fences for added privacy. An outstanding location in the heart of cosmopolitan Coburg, it's walking distance to Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants, close to local schools, Coburg Station and the area's renowned retail precinct. Description:
Go your own way.
Whether buying your first home or looking to invest, there's plenty to recommend this elevated two bedroom unit graced with northerly light and a great courtyard. Opening into a living room with reverse cycle air conditioning, it also offers a kitchen/meals with a glass-ceramic cooktop, fan forced oven and dishwasher. Beyond the kitchen is a paved courtyard starring a vibrant camellia tree and space to dine alfresco. Double bedrooms feature BIRs, one looks out to the courtyard and the other is bathed in northerly light. The central bathroom teams with a concealed laundry while polished floorboards and a carport broaden appeal. South of Bell Street, moments to McDonald Reserve, it's a stroll to transport, schools, Coburg Market and Sydney Road.

Description:
Absolute Opulence and Architectural Excellence
Brand-new and beautifully appointed, this stunning residence sets the benchmark in low-maintenance family luxury with its spacious and versatile floorplan, designer details throughout and outstanding Brunswick-edge convenience. Meticulously-detailed interior showcases four bedrooms (large master with fully-fitted WIR and private balcony), two luxurious ensuites, equally-stylish main bathroom and guest powder room (fourth WC) - all with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a dedicated study area with built-in workstations, expansive open-plan living/dining area and gourmet kitchen with stone benchtops/splashbacks, breakfast bar, ample cupboard space and premium Smeg appliances. Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling throughout, comprehensive security system (alarm, CCTV and video intercom), high square-set ceilings, double-glazed windows and Blackbutt solid timber floors, large laundry and excellent storage options throughout. Stacker doors from the living area reveal a fabulous al-fresco entertaining deck and private back garden, plus the added advantage of an internally-accessed garage via gated driveway (both remote-controlled). The best of Coburg at your fingertips, it's walking distance to trams (Sydney Road and Moreland Road), Moreland Station, local schools, as well as an endless array of shops, cafes and restaurants.

Expressions of Interest closes 10th September at 5:00pm
Ideally located in one of Coburg's premier streets, this first floor apartment is perfectly positioned close to Sydney Road & Nicholson Street tram lines, a diverse choice of eateries and shopping on cosmopolitan Sydney Road and Nicholson Street.
Set at the rear of the block with security entrance access this studio offers open living with kitchenette, stainless steel appliances & granite bench top. Tiled bathroom with shower and vanity plus ample natural light shining through.
Approximately a kilometer from the lifestyle advantages of wetlands and the bike and walking tracks along the Merri Creek it offers an exceptional opportunity for first home buyers, downsizers or investors to secure a fabulous property on the city's edge.
Insights: 8/27 The Grove, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019.

Description:
Sale of the Century
Enjoyed, enhanced and meticulously maintained by generations of the one family for over 100 years, this heritage Edwardian (c1918) provides a lifestyle of immediate quality and enviable urban convenience along with plenty of room for future expansion (STCA). Surrounded by lush gardens, the home's impeccably-presented interior comprises a wide central hallway accessing three large bedrooms and elegant lounge/fourth bedroom, plus a spotless bathroom and separate WC, open family/dining area and adjoining timber-top kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Additional features include ducted heating and split-system a/c, high ornate ceilings and solid timber floors, alarm, 4kW solar power system, full-size laundry and large linen cupboard. Step outside to discover a delightfully deep backyard complete with lush gardens, working veggie patches and established fruit trees, extensive brick paving, handy workshop/storeroom and multiple watertanks (approx 20,000L in total). A prime position walking distance to a choice of tram lines, Moreland Station, Sydney Road's endless cafes and restaurants, as well as shops and supermarkets, popular schools, parks and Merri Creek trails. Land size: 12.19 x 35.05= 427sqm (approx)
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 62 Barrow Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Smart thinking
Smartly presented, this two bedroom apartment is set to entice market entrants and investors. One of only eight apartments and situated on the first floor, it highlights an open living/meals illuminated by a large north-facing window. Bifold doors lead to the adjoining kitchen, which flaunts a new gas stove and everything else you might need to create memorable meals. Big bedrooms host built-in robes and the central bathroom also functions as a laundry. An intercom system has been installed and there's a dedicated off street parking space, guarded by an electric gate. Easy to maintain and enjoy, this appealing apartment is in a great spot close to transport and cafes, handy to cosmopolitan Sydney Road and only a short drive to CityLink access for quick commutes to the city's heart.

Description:
Ideal Location
Boasting a desirable city fringe location with street appeal to match, this beautifully presented three bedroom residence is an ideal starter or a rewarding opportunity for astute investors.
A stroll to lively Sydney Road or minutes to the city it features polished floorboards, alfresco courtyard and automated double garage offering direct internal access.
The light-filled open plan living and dining flows seamlessly into the smart kitchen displaying stainless steel appliances and white Fisher and Paykel dishwasher. There are three double bedrooms presenting built-in-robes, plus family bathroom with recessed shower, bath, vanity, storage and toilet. Extras comprise study nook, automated awning, laundry with 2nd shower, separate toilet and reverse cycle heating/cooling units. Moments to transport, bike paths and Leisure centre, its handy!

Description:
'Bethany'
Featuring prized dual street frontage, 'Bethany' is a four bedroom Californian Bungalow proudly presiding over approximately 490m2 in a great locale and in comfortable condition . Beyond a picturesque facade adorned with leadlight, the family home comprises a sitting room, kitchen, vast living/dining and large covered outdoor entertaining area. Boasting a 900mm Ilve stove and waterfall stone benchtop, the kitchen comes complete with a canopy rangehood, abundant storage and a dishwasher. Bedrooms are large, most host a built-in or walk-in robe, ceilings are lofty and there's heating/cooling. Offering a front driveway, remote controlled vehicle access from both streets (including to a carport) and various future options, 'Bethany' is a stroll to cafes, schools, trams and parks and convenient to thriving Sydney Road.

Description:
Stylish and Secluded in Coburg's Heartland
One of only three, this contemporary two-level townhouse is set to impress with its quality features, well-proportioned rooms and abundance of natural light - perfectly positioned for ultimate urban convenience offering immediate access to Coburg's key lifestyle attractions. Immaculately presented, this low maintenance & modern quality residence is sure to impress. gleaming polished timber floors and a bright north-facing living zone welcome you upon entry, followed by a stylish kitchen boasting stainless-steel Blanco appliances, stone bench-tops and efficient user-friendly storage overlooking a private courtyard. Cleverly concealed Euro style laundry and separate study downstairs further demonstrates effectiveness. Modern central bathroom and two double bedrooms upstairs both with BIRs. Heating & air-conditioning throughout, down stairs powder room & extra storage under stair case. Easy access to secure carport via the rear. Only minutes away from exciting shopping of Sydney Road and public transport providing easy access into the CBD.

Description:
Value-Packed Entry into Coburg's Premier Pocket
A wide tree-lined street in Coburg's exclusive Moreland Park enclave provides the perfect setting for this mid-century villa (one of only five) offering a terrific lifestyle/investment opportunity with its immediate comfort and convenience and exciting renovation potential. Filled with northerly light, the home's impeccable interior comprises two bedrooms (large master) both with built-in robes, central bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious front lounge through to the separate kitchen/meals area and full-size laundry. Features include cooling, security shutters, solid hardwood floors, plus a wide rear courtyard with high fences for added privacy and undercover parking space on title. Easy access to a range of attractions and amenities including shops and supermarkets, local schools, cafes and an endless array of restaurants as well as Merri Creek trails and parkland, Moreland Station and choice of tramlines to university/hospital precincts and the CBD.

Description:
The living is easy.
Sunlit, spacious and the rear of only two homes, this elevated two bedroom villa unit is destined to delight. Attractively presented in a quiet and appealing position, it offers a living room with street views, generous kitchen/dining and easily maintained courtyard, where a covered area waits to host incredible meals with friends. Stainless steel appliances are ready to create delicious meals from day one, highlighting a four burner gas cooktop with wok burner and fan forced electric oven. Double bedrooms offer built-in robes, the dual entry bathroom is centrally placed, plus there's a convenient separate toilet, laundry, heating/cooling, polished floorboards and garage. Transport, Bush Reserve and schools are a stroll and vibrant Coburg Market/Sydney Road only a 3 minute drive.

Description:
Extended Elegance amid Gorgeous Garden Surrounds
So much Moore than meets the eye! This classic Californian retains its authentic allure while delivering a contemporary family lifestyle of quality and versatility with its expanded floorplan and long list of added features - all in a prime location moments from parkland and Merri Creek trails. Immaculately presented from start to finish, the home's light-filled interior comprises three generous bedrooms (two with built-in robes) and contemporary-style bathroom, elegant central lounge leading through to the open dining/living area and adjoining kitchen with stainless steel benchtops, stainless steel cooking appliances and double dish drawer. Other highlights include hydronic heating throughout, solar power and solar hot water, original lead-light windows, high ceilings and solid timber floors, laundry with ironing cupboard and second WC. Double doors reveal a fabulous entertaining deck and wonderfully private north-facing backyard complete with established gardens and fruit trees, watertanks, secure storage shed and carport. Close proximity to a range of lifestyle attractions including local cafes and schools, shops and supermarkets, an endless array of restaurants as well as a choice of tramlines to university/hospital precincts and the CBD.
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Period Presence in the Heart of Historic Newlands
In a heritage streetscape surrounded by classic mid-century homes, this freestanding residence occupies a uniquely deep block of land providing an environment of indoor style and outdoor space along with impressive options to expand in the future (STCA). Enhanced interior highlights three bedrooms (all with mirrored robes) and updated central bathroom with spa bath, spacious lounge leading through to the updated kitchen/meals area with timber benchtops, Ilve oven and DeLonghi dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, open fireplace (lounge) and additional ceiling fans (all bedrooms), solid hardwood floors, laundry with ample storage cupboards and separate WC. Outside, discover an undercover entertaining deck overlooking the expansive backyard garden complete with air-conditioned bungalow/studio, established trees, large watertank, gazebo and storage shed, plus front double carport. Merri Creek trails and parkland at the end of the street, it's also walking distance to Coburg Lake and swimming pool, Murray Road buses and Coburg High School, as well as easy access to Nicholson Street trams and Coburg Hill Shopping Centre.
